Hey, Mr. Etesami!

24
00:02:50,743 --> 00:02:51,001
Rana, Missy!

25
00:02:51,734 --> 00:02:52,369
Come on out!

26
00:02:53,002 --> 00:02:54,937
The building's about to collapse.

27
00:03:03,471 --> 00:03:05,774
Woman: The building's falling apart.
Get out of there!

28
00:03:06,607 --> 00:03:08,276
What's going on?!

29
00:03:09,109 --> 00:03:11,144
What are you doing here, honey?
Come here, honey.

30
00:03:12,178 --> 00:03:13,249
Why? What's going on?

31
00:03:14,282 --> 00:03:17,685
Mr. Etesami evacuate the building.
It's collapsing. Hurry up!

32
00:03:19,618 --> 00:03:21,153
- Let's go, everyone!
- Rana!.. Rana!

33
00:03:21,355 --> 00:03:23,323
- What's going on, Emad?
- Come here, Rana! Hurry up!

34
00:03:26,324 --> 00:03:28,624
Let's go, man!

35
00:03:29,357 --> 00:03:32,524
- What's going on, Mr. Fallah?
- I don't know. Just evacuate, man!

36
00:03:33,558 --> 00:03:36,294
Rana!.. Hurry up!
Come on!

37
00:03:38,127 --> 00:03:40,062
- What is it?
- Go down! Go, go!

38
00:03:41,495 --> 00:03:43,028
Nasim!..
Chop, chop, Nasim!

39
00:03:43,058 --> 00:03:45,030
Mr. Amiri, let's go!
Evacuate!

40
00:03:48,663 --> 00:03:51,501
Emad, son!..
For God's sake someone help my baby.

41
00:03:51,531 --> 00:03:52,832
I'm coming, wait.

42
00:03:54,533 --> 00:03:55,933
Here, here, put this on.

43
00:03:56,065 --> 00:03:57,067
What?..
Let me come with you.

44
00:03:57,097 --> 00:03:58,600
No, you can't.
Just go down to the alley.

45
00:03:59,204 --> 00:04:00,318
Go tell everyone to go to the alley.

46
00:04:00,348 --> 00:04:01,339
Mrs. Samimi!..
Mrs. Samimi!

47
00:04:02,140 --> 00:04:05,640
- Where's Hossein?
- I can't get him out of there.

48
00:04:11,631 --> 00:04:15,755
Hossein get up, my boy!
The house is coming down.

49
00:04:15,785 --> 00:04:18,534
Get up, Hossein!.. Get up!

50
00:04:18,667 --> 00:04:23,103
- Emad, come on, everyone's gone.
- Go down to the alley. Go tell everyone.

51
00:04:24,104 --> 00:04:25,804
Mr. Fallah, get everyone down to the alley.

52
00:04:26,937 --> 00:04:29,474
Come on, Hossein!..
what are they doing?!

53
00:04:33,107 --> 00:04:36,576
- Glasses... my glasses...
- I'll bring your glasses.

54
00:04:56,077 --> 00:05:02,112
The Salesman Written and
Directed by Asghar Farhadi

55
00:05:10,945 --> 00:05:11,623
Guys!..

56
00:05:11,653 --> 00:05:15,215
There's no need to
bring all your stuff.

57
00:05:15,749 --> 00:05:18,018
- We've got everything down in our place.
- Okay.

58
00:05:21,652 --> 00:05:24,587
- I can't find it.
- I don't know, just look around.

59
00:05:24,721 --> 00:05:26,457
- You want me to take these?
- Yeah, thanks a lot.

60
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:28,759
I thought you were supposed to just
bring your towel and toothbrushes?

61
00:05:28,792 --> 00:05:30,360
The towel and the brushes
are in there too.

62
00:05:33,860 --> 00:05:35,860
- Did you lock the car?
- Yeah.

63
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,960
Ah, keys, keys!..
Gimme the keys.

64
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:40,360
Here.

65
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:42,600
Guys!

66
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:46,610
Hey

67
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:47,125
Hey Kati.
Hi.

68
00:05:47,155 --> 00:05:48,182
What's up, Kati?

69
00:05:48,212 --> 00:05:49,210
You're alive?!

70
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:51,247
The way Sia said the
house has collapsed,

71
00:05:51,277 --> 00:05:53,920
I thought we'd have to drag
you from under the ruins.

72
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,800
Oh, whoa!..
What's going on here?!

73
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:59,440
There's smell of gas...

74
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:01,770
It's from last night.

75
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,720
Well, then, get your stuff.
Let's get out of here.

76
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:08,840
Hey.

77
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,810
Why did you come up?

78
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:12,880
Cut off the electricity,
this is dripping.

79
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,800
I can't find the card, man.

80
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:27,840
Well, see if it's between your
documents and stuff.

81
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:30,400
Kati, dear, don't go there,
it's dangerous.

82
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:33,400
Oh, my God...

83
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:39,260
<i>You could only hear the sobbing
of Mashti Hassan's wife,</i>

84
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:42,361
<i>... sitting alone with her lit lantern
on the stable's roof</i>

85
00:06:42,460 --> 00:06:44,880
<i>and the desperate moans of a cow
from inside the stable.</i>

86
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:47,730
Sir! is it a true story?

87
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:51,540
True? No, but you could say that
in a way, in Saedi's stories

88
00:06:51,641 --> 00:06:57,740
the scenery, the type of characters,
and relationships are real. Very real.

89
00:06:57,770 --> 00:06:59,000
Sir, how can someone turn into a cow?

90
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:00,880
Try looking in the mirror.

91
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,180
You think you're funny, huh?

92
00:07:03,780 --> 00:07:06,100
But seriously, Sir,
how does a person turn into a cow?

93
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:09,600
Gradually...

94
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:12,240
Sir, are we gonna watch the film
of this story too?

95
00:07:12,340 --> 00:07:13,700
Yeah, that's a good idea.

96
00:07:13,801 --> 00:07:16,801
Maybe I bring it next time and
we can watch it together.

97
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:17,320
Yes?

98
00:07:17,420 --> 00:07:18,680
Sir, when can we see your play?

99
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:20,240
The performance begins next week.

100
00:07:20,341 --> 00:07:24,441
Once we've had a few days to settle in,
I'll definitely invite you all to come.

101
00:07:24,540 --> 00:07:25,660
- Thank you, Sir!
- What's it called, Sir?

102
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:26,840
"Death of a Salesman",
who's read it?

103
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,400
"The enemy"!

104
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:31,960
Jokes aside,
have any of you read it?

105
00:07:31,990 --> 00:07:33,840
Sir, who's the author?

106
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:34,720
Arthur Miller

107
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:36,440
Hmm... no, I've not.

108
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:38,170
Very good.

109
00:07:38,470 --> 00:07:40,740
Excuse me, boys.

110
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:42,440
Yes?

111
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,440
Hello.

112
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:46,440
Yes.

113
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:49,770
Sorry, I can't talk right now,
I'm in class.

114
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:52,960
If you call back in 10
minutes, I'll be free.

115
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:57,560
Yeah, with stick shifts... Silver...

116
00:07:59,461 --> 00:08:00,661
Sure... that's fine.

117
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,960
Sir, what's your role?

118
00:08:03,990 --> 00:08:05,240
The Salesman.

119
00:08:05,340 --> 00:08:08,680
- What are you selling, Sir?
- Potatoes!

120
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:10,540
When you come,
you'll see for yourselves.

121
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:11,970
What's it's model, Sir?

122
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,490
- What?
- Your Peugeot 206, you know.

123
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:16,060
- Why do you wanna know?
- Aren't you selling, Sir?

124
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:19,740
Sir, his dad's a parking officer,
just tell him to scrap your fines for you.

125
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:21,900
Do you even commit driving offenses, Sir?

126
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:24,960
Sir, why do Iranians call BMWs
"Bee-Em-Veh"s?

127
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:27,240
I didn't hear you.

128
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:30,320
Why do Iranians call BMWs
"Bee-Em-Veh"s?

129
00:08:30,621 --> 00:08:33,821
- Get outa here!
- Dude, just zip it!

130
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:39,400
That's alright. He doesn't know,
so he's asking.

131
00:08:39,430 --> 00:08:40,940
I don't know either.

132
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:45,100
Guys... eh, for your next session...

133
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:50,980
I want a summary of this story.
I don't want any excuses, like...

134
00:08:50,981 --> 00:08:54,581
"I fell asleep, we had guests",
and... stuff like that.

135
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:08,100
Mister, could you please
scooch over a bit?

136
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:22,520
Sir, can I sit in front and
this young man sits back here?

137
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,320
Father...

138
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:53,240
Somebody in there?

139
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:57,800
No, I think the noise was
from the next door.

140
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:01,160
- No, no, somebody got in your bathroom!
- No, there's no one there.

141
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:05,000
It’s the next room, there’s a party.
These kind of noises are normal...

142
00:10:05,030 --> 00:10:06,800
Can I come out?

143
00:10:08,901 --> 00:10:10,301
There’s something moving
in the bathtub, Willy!

144
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:17,827
Ah, Miss Francis,
you better go back to your room.

145
00:10:17,857 --> 00:10:20,073
They must be finished
painting by now.

146
00:10:20,103 --> 00:10:22,320
But I can't, I’ve got to get dressed first!

147
00:10:22,350 --> 00:10:24,740
Yes, you can, you can!
Please!

148
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:28,570
Biff, this is Miss Francis,
my next-door neighbor.

149
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:33,140
They were painting her room.
And she asked to come and use the bath.

150
00:10:33,341 --> 00:10:37,841
And I said, that's alright,
So, I let her take a shower here.

151
00:10:37,940 --> 00:10:38,960
You can go back to your room now.

152
00:10:39,060 --> 00:10:40,530
But Willy, I don't have any clothes on!

153
00:10:40,560 --> 00:10:43,340
Please, get out of here!
Go back to your room.

154
00:10:43,940 --> 00:10:45,800
You promised me stockings, Willy!

155
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:47,780
I have no stockings here!

156
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:50,500
Why?! You had two boxes of size 9s for me,
and I want them, Willy!

157
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:53,480
Alright, take one and go.
For God’s sake, will you get outa here!

158
00:10:53,981 --> 00:10:54,981
Please!

159
00:10:55,060 --> 00:10:56,080
Go!

160
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:13,320
I just hope there’s nobody in the hall.
I can't go out without any clothes!

161
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:23,000
By the way, are you
football or...

162
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:26,320
Dammit!

163
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:28,320
Siavash!

164
00:11:29,020 --> 00:11:30,420
What happened, mom?

165
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:32,133
I do my best to ignore it but he
keeps getting worse every night!

166
00:11:32,163 --> 00:11:33,020
Sadra, dear, come down, let's go!

167
00:11:33,340 --> 00:11:34,740
Sanam, dear, just ignore him.

168
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:36,840
He thinks just because I'm playing a whore,
he can do whatever he wants.

169
00:11:36,870 --> 00:11:38,160
What's that got to do with it?

170
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:39,900
Why don't you laugh at the others then, huh?

171
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,340
- I was laughing at your clothes, not you...
- Shut up! Shut the hell up!

172
00:11:43,660 --> 00:11:44,500
Siavash, come here!

173
00:11:44,780 --> 00:11:46,960
Sanam, don't be childish on
this final night. Sanam...

174
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:50,300
Alright, I'm freaking sorry...
I'm sorry.

175
00:11:50,660 --> 00:11:53,257
In this cold, rehearsing every night,
with this child.

176
00:11:53,287 --> 00:11:54,120
Let's go, honey.

177
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:56,720
You just had to fuck it up,
didn't you?

178
00:11:56,820 --> 00:11:57,470
What's that got to do with us?

179
00:11:57,500 --> 00:11:58,020
It's your own husband.

180
00:11:58,120 --> 00:12:00,120
Let me take the k...

181
00:12:00,150 --> 00:12:02,090
Let go!

182
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,785
Sanam don't...

183
00:12:03,815 --> 00:12:05,450
I said get off!

184
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:06,120
I was kidding...
I said get off!

185
00:12:06,150 --> 00:12:07,360
I was kidding...

186
00:12:11,161 --> 00:12:12,361
- I was messing with you.
- Where are you going?

187
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:17,157
Comes out of the shower with a raincoat,
and says,

188
00:12:17,187 --> 00:12:19,960
"How can I go out
without any clothes?"

189
00:12:22,880 --> 00:12:24,960
I can't, man,
it makes me laugh.

190
00:12:25,060 --> 00:12:26,720
Go after her or she'll get annoyed
and won't come tomorrow.

191
00:12:26,940 --> 00:12:30,700
Don't make me go out without clothes!
I'm shy!

192
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:33,880
Come on, how can I go out
without any cloth...

193
00:12:33,910 --> 00:12:34,290
Sanam!

194
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,880
The guy's totally nuts!

195
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:47,210
Did you find a place?

196
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:51,560
60 sq. metres, 3rd floor, no elevator.
40 mils in front, 600k tomans per month.

197
00:12:51,590 --> 00:12:53,140
- Where?
- Amiratabak

198
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:56,140
- What sort of a place are you looking for?
- Something temporary...

199
00:12:56,780 --> 00:12:57,694
...If we can't find anywhere,

200
00:12:57,724 --> 00:12:59,900
We have to bring our stuff,
and live right in the middle of the stage.

201
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:02,840
You free tomorrow afternoon?

202
00:13:03,140 --> 00:13:04,040
How come?

203
00:13:04,340 --> 00:13:05,360
I'm taking you somewhere.

204
00:13:05,460 --> 00:13:08,620
Come on guys...
once more from the top, no interruptions.

205
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:13,160
You tired?

206
00:13:13,190 --> 00:13:15,130
Nope

207
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:18,005
Oh, you're here too!

208
00:13:18,035 --> 00:13:20,880
Aww kitty!
Who's this?

209
00:13:21,281 --> 00:13:22,981
Come here, you!

210
00:13:26,782 --> 00:13:30,382
He's tame... What's up, kitty?

211
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:37,060
This place is cool!

212
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:06,840
Babak

213
00:14:08,740 --> 00:14:09,980
Is that the storage room?

214
00:14:11,640 --> 00:14:12,980
- Which one?
- This

215
00:14:13,300 --> 00:14:14,960
No! It's the second bedroom

216
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:16,880
- Really?!
- Well, yeah.

217
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:19,660
- Isn't it too small?
- It's a two-bedroom!

218
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:20,700
So it's good?

219
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:22,880
You're just two people,
what do you need all this space for anyways?

220
00:14:22,940 --> 00:14:24,380
Watch your mouth, "two people"!

221
00:14:24,410 --> 00:14:26,640
Who knows,
maybe we end up being three people...

222
00:14:27,740 --> 00:14:30,000
Rana, is he serious?

223
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:31,180
No, come on!

224
00:14:31,580 --> 00:14:32,880
- He doesn't look like it.
- Why is that?

225
00:14:33,580 --> 00:14:34,700
Is this door locked?
Is it locked?

226
00:14:35,980 --> 00:14:37,960
The previous tenant's stuff is in there;
they're supposed to be collecting it.

227
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:42,120
Don't be scared kitty, it's just me.

228
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:50,760
- How long's it been vacant?
- Three weeks.

229
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:00,820
What are they doing to this city?

230
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:05,640
I wish we could tear it
all down and start again

231
00:15:05,940 --> 00:15:09,720
They've already destroyed and rebuilt it,
and look how it's turned out...

232
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:11,085
Babak?

233
00:15:11,115 --> 00:15:11,850
Yes dear

234
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:13,530
God have mercy on us.

235
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:15,137
When do you think they'll
clear their stuff out?

236
00:15:15,167 --> 00:15:17,080
They promised they'll be
here in the next day or two

237
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:30,760
There's no parking, you'll have to
leave your car on the street.

238
00:15:30,860 --> 00:15:31,619
We don't need parking anyways.

239
00:15:31,649 --> 00:15:33,040
We're selling our car to pay
your mortgage down payment.

240
00:15:33,070 --> 00:15:34,210
Who mentioned money?

241
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:35,380
Well, either way...

242
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:37,440
Hello
Hello Mr Salimi.

243
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:39,960
One of the good things about this
place are Mr. Shanazari and his wife.

244
00:15:40,260 --> 00:15:41,570
- Hello.
- Hello, how're you doing?

245
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:44,720
- Hello.
- Hello, hello. how do you do Ma'am?

246
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:47,820
Babak, which one's the storage?

247
00:15:48,420 --> 00:15:49,820
It's here, come, take a look.

248
00:15:54,780 --> 00:15:55,210
- Mr Salimi?
- Yes?

249
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:57,760
The door's open, take a look.

250
00:16:00,620 --> 00:16:03,880
Please make sure it doesn't
turn out like the last one.

251
00:16:03,980 --> 00:16:05,840
- No, come on, I know these guys.
- You said you knew the last ones too.

252
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:07,840
Don't worry about it.

253
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:11,120
- Babak, what do they do?
- They're my friends, they're into arts.

254
00:16:11,260 --> 00:16:11,820
I hope so

255
00:16:11,940 --> 00:16:13,240
It's okay for a few months.

256
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:18,360
Just make sure he lets us pay him for it.
No favors.

257
00:16:19,160 --> 00:16:21,880
Looks like we've finally caught a break.

258
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:29,520
Careful, don't rush

259
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:32,620
- You need help, Sir?
- No, you go ahead and bring the rest.

260
00:16:42,740 --> 00:16:44,800
Just be careful not to hit the light-bulb.

261
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:48,640
Sorry sir, thanks for the help.

262
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:54,480
- Are the keys here too?
- They took that one room's with 'em.

263
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:03,740
Where's Ali?

264
00:17:13,120 --> 00:17:13,640
Ali...

265
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:14,170
Yep?

266
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:17,140
For God's sake, leave that alone,
I'll call an electrician tomorrow.

267
00:17:17,420 --> 00:17:18,820
It'll only take a second

268
00:17:18,921 --> 00:17:20,240
Leave it, man!

269
00:17:21,020 --> 00:17:24,260
If she'd said, we wouldn't have hired
the truck and the movers.

270
00:17:24,740 --> 00:17:26,558
How was I supposed to know?

271
00:17:26,588 --> 00:17:30,360
She sounded so sure that I
didn't think she'd bail on us.

272
00:17:32,740 --> 00:17:33,990
So, what's she saying now?

273
00:17:34,020 --> 00:17:35,920
Hasn't answered
ever since this morning.

274
00:17:36,140 --> 00:17:37,960
Why don't you try from a different number?

275
00:17:38,740 --> 00:17:40,860
Bring your phone Nana.

276
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:45,800
We really need that room,
we've brought a pickup full our things.

277
00:17:49,860 --> 00:17:51,260
Yes

278
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:53,960
Okay

279
00:17:54,860 --> 00:17:57,200
He's here if you like to speak to him,

280
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:03,940
Thanks

281
00:18:05,660 --> 00:18:07,320
Says, she's said all
she has to say to you.

282
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:08,840
Well, what did she say?

283
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:12,161
She signed the contract on
a new place two days ago,

284
00:18:12,191 --> 00:18:14,400
but the landlord bucked
at the last moment,

285
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:17,680
She's looking for a place, but can't come
for her stuff until she finds somewhere.

286
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,780
She said to tell you not to
let anyone touch her stuff. Please.

287
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:29,120
Oh, yeah, and she doesn't want
to talk to you again.

288
00:18:30,660 --> 00:18:31,700
Any news? What happened?

289
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:34,080
I don't know, nothing for now.
Let me take it, Kati.

290
00:18:36,420 --> 00:18:37,760
Ali

291
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:39,980
- Yes?
- You got a screwdriver in your car?

292
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:50,120
This is enough stuff for a bride's dowry!

293
00:18:50,620 --> 00:18:51,980
I thought it was just
a few bits and pieces.

294
00:18:52,980 --> 00:18:55,160
- Maybe we should leave it...
- It's fine, I'll take responsibility for it

295
00:18:55,461 --> 00:18:57,561
Alright, boys,
let's move those things over there.

296
00:19:06,160 --> 00:19:07,320
Rana...

297
00:19:08,320 --> 00:19:10,720
<i>mumbling</i>

298
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,170
These are people's belongings

299
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:16,280
What do you want me to do? It's been
3 days now. She keeps saying...

300
00:19:16,380 --> 00:19:17,940
... "I'm coming today, I'll come tomorrow."

301
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:18,800
What if she shows up?

302
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:22,080
Well she should've kept her word then.
Never mind. Come on!

303
00:19:22,110 --> 00:19:24,120
Guys, I can't carry anything heavy!

304
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,320
Mr?

305
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:44,960
Come on, let's eat.

306
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:49,080
Rana, dear!

307
00:19:49,180 --> 00:19:49,800
Yes dear?

308
00:19:51,420 --> 00:19:53,960
Honey... the charger.

309
00:19:54,761 --> 00:19:58,861
<i>I'll turn into words,
run through your ears...</i>

310
00:19:58,862 --> 00:20:01,362
<i>I'll turn into thoughts,
stick in your head...</i>

311
00:20:01,462 --> 00:20:04,862
<i>I'll be a Benz,
race under your feet...</i>

312
00:20:04,863 --> 00:20:08,563
<i>I'll be poverty
in your purse...</i>

313
00:20:08,763 --> 00:20:10,863
<i>I'll be a wolf,
raid your herd.</i>

314
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:53,960
You two, go to the door and
bring over one of those boxes.

315
00:20:53,990 --> 00:20:55,730
Hi guys

316
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:57,410
Are these your 206's car parts, Sir?

317
00:20:57,440 --> 00:20:57,646
Put these in front of
the principal's office,

318
00:20:57,676 --> 00:20:57,810
tell the librarian to come see me.

319
00:20:57,840 --> 00:20:59,294
Put these in front of
the principal's office,

320
00:20:59,324 --> 00:21:00,480
tell the librarian to come see me.

321
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:04,640
Very good guys, I want the poem
memorized for next time.

322
00:21:04,670 --> 00:21:05,520
Okay.

323
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:06,760
Thank you.

324
00:21:07,520 --> 00:21:09,000
Bye, Sir.

325
00:21:09,030 --> 00:21:11,000
Bye.

326
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:38,080
- Bye, Sir!
- So, long.

327
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:42,065
Thanks Sir

328
00:21:42,095 --> 00:21:43,720
Goodbye

329
00:21:45,780 --> 00:21:48,940
- Sir, can I say something?
- What?

330
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:50,840
Sir, I was really pissed off the other day.

331
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:52,080
Which day?

332
00:21:52,240 --> 00:21:55,600
The day that woman insulted you
in the Taxi.

333
00:21:57,360 --> 00:21:58,770
Was it an insult?

334
00:21:58,800 --> 00:22:02,890
You know, that she said,
she wants to sit in the front seat.

335
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:07,440
Sir, after you got out of the car,
I told them that you were my teacher.

336
00:22:07,470 --> 00:22:10,560
And that we all love you so much.
Like, all the guys.

337
00:22:11,760 --> 00:22:13,200
What was your first name again?

338
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:14,580
Amin..

339
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:21,040
Amin, you can be sure, some guy had
done something to her in a taxi before...

340
00:22:21,141 --> 00:22:23,941
...to make her think
that way about everyone.

341
00:22:24,920 --> 00:22:27,560
Don't worry about it, it's just
the first 100 years that are tough.

342
00:22:27,590 --> 00:22:28,450
See you

343
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:28,720
Bye
See you

344
00:22:28,750 --> 00:22:29,400
Bye

345
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:09,240
Okay

346
00:23:12,541 --> 00:23:14,341
Of all the time...

347
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:18,360
I don't know what to do with her.

348
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:19,760
Who?

349
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:21,600
This woman

350
00:23:21,880 --> 00:23:24,495
I called to ask when she'll
clear her stuff out.

351
00:23:24,525 --> 00:23:26,640
She got angry, started threatening...

352
00:23:26,670 --> 00:23:27,800
Over what?

353
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:32,080
"Why did you touch my personal things?
those were my private stuff...

354
00:23:32,110 --> 00:23:32,810
... I'll sue you.."

355
00:23:32,840 --> 00:23:35,940
Last night I was running around, saving
her stuff from the rain, up until morning.

356
00:23:35,970 --> 00:23:36,880
Her problem's something else...

357
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:39,580
- Who Babak, the woman?
- Yeah.

358
00:23:40,180 --> 00:23:41,740
When's she coming to get her stuff?

359
00:23:42,340 --> 00:23:43,700
Says, whenever she finds a place.

360
00:23:47,580 --> 00:23:49,960
Sadra darling, come here with me.
Hurry up.

361
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:55,800
Hurry up guys, the audience will
be in in five minutes.

362
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:06,675
Emad... Emad, they're coming here
again after the performance.

363
00:24:06,705 --> 00:24:10,580
They've approved 3 of the 6 revisions,
there's another three left.

364
00:24:10,581 --> 00:24:12,281
if you stay around after the performance,
you can talk to them.

365
00:24:12,380 --> 00:24:12,880
Tonight after the performance?

366
00:24:12,910 --> 00:24:13,270
Yes

367
00:24:13,300 --> 00:24:15,130
If it helps, I'll stay.

368
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:17,340
Sure, or else there's a chance they
might cancel the whole show tomorrow.

369
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:17,840
How many did they say?

370
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:19,440
Three... Guys will you please hurry up!

371
00:24:19,840 --> 00:24:20,520
I'll go, then.

372
00:24:21,620 --> 00:24:22,320
Won't you wait around?

373
00:24:22,460 --> 00:24:25,060
No, you'll be stuck here
until around midnight.

374
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:26,800
Take the car, then.

375
00:24:26,900 --> 00:24:28,400
Where are the house keys?

376
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:29,995
In my coat's pocket.

377
00:24:30,025 --> 00:24:31,420
Have a good performance

378
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:32,280
You too!

379
00:26:11,120 --> 00:26:13,940
Say, on your way back, if
the supermarket's open...

380
00:26:13,941 --> 00:26:15,541
... buy something, we've got
nothing for breakfast.

381
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:20,520
Yes, I said if it's open. If it's open!

382
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:25,960
Also, pick up some hand sanitizer.

383
00:26:27,461 --> 00:26:29,561
Maybe I take a shower
until you get here.

384
00:26:29,940 --> 00:26:33,540
No not at all, I'm a mess. I haven't
even wiped off my stage makeup.

385
00:26:36,660 --> 00:26:40,300
I'll be out soon... soon.

386
00:26:41,201 --> 00:26:43,001
Yup... love you, bye.

387
00:27:36,520 --> 00:27:37,250
Anything else?

388
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:38,280
That's all, thanks.

389
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:41,320
Be my guest.
Are you paying by card?

390
00:27:41,350 --> 00:27:42,840
No, cash.

391
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:56,040
Hello Ma'am

392
00:27:56,070 --> 00:27:56,480
Hello?

393
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:58,890
Good evening, I'm your upstairs neighbor.

394
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:02,320
We've just moved in,
could you open the door please?

395
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:04,200
Thank you.

396
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:22,280
Rana?

397
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:25,200
Rana?

398
00:28:28,120 --> 00:28:29,320
Rana?

399
00:28:58,800 --> 00:28:59,730
Rana!

400
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:01,105
What happened to you?

401
00:29:01,135 --> 00:29:02,450
Please step outside, Sir.

402
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:05,960
You can't be in here, Sir.
We'll call you when for the CT scan.

403
00:29:07,160 --> 00:29:07,680
Wait outside, please.

404
00:29:07,700 --> 00:29:08,160
Look at me Rana...

405
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:13,840
Everything's fine,
I'll call you for the CT scan... Please.

406
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:19,800
Make sure you change the locks
first thing tomorrow.

407
00:29:20,960 --> 00:29:24,560
Why? Did someone get into the house?

408
00:29:24,861 --> 00:29:26,561
I thought she'd fainted,
was dizzy or...

409
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:28,040
We don't know what happened yet

410
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:31,760
All of a sudden we heard shouting
and screaming from upstairs.

411
00:29:31,860 --> 00:29:35,640
Not like, normal, not once,
scream after scream...

412
00:29:35,641 --> 00:29:37,634
I told him go upstairs and check,

413
00:29:37,664 --> 00:29:40,441
he said,
couples get into fights all the time.

414
00:29:40,740 --> 00:29:43,160
Then we heard some heavy
bangs in the stairs,

415
00:29:43,190 --> 00:29:45,940
I told him "Muhammad,
God knows, something's up."

416
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:46,520
Who was it?

417
00:29:46,620 --> 00:29:50,700
By the time we reached the stairs,
we just saw someone fleeing up the street.

418
00:29:50,860 --> 00:29:53,080
I don't know what happened to his foot,
but it had bled all over the stairs.

419
00:29:53,110 --> 00:29:56,780
If I'd caught him, he'd be dead now.

420
00:29:57,480 --> 00:30:00,620
Then we went upstairs and
found your wife unconscious...

421
00:30:00,621 --> 00:30:04,121
there was blood all over the bathroom floor.
I dressed her and brought her here.

422
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:07,290
Never mind that, thank God
something worse didn't happen.

423
00:30:07,320 --> 00:30:13,520
Woman, do us a favour, go to the ER,
and check if there's any news or something.

424
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:18,520
Sorry about putting you to all this trouble.

425
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:20,960
Have a seat, sit down, son.

426
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:28,580
Was anything missing from the house?

427
00:30:29,040 --> 00:30:31,800
I don't know.
I didn't notice anything.

428
00:30:32,360 --> 00:30:35,640
I don't think it was a robbery.
What would a thief be doing in the bathroom?

429
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:38,290
Then who was it?

430
00:30:38,320 --> 00:30:40,560
The guy was one of
that woman's customers.

431
00:30:40,590 --> 00:30:41,800
Who? What woman?

432
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:44,480
The woman who lived there
before you moving in.

433
00:30:46,100 --> 00:30:49,640
Tell you the truth, she
was kind of messed up...

434
00:30:50,141 --> 00:30:53,441
... and I think, the guy came here
on account of her still being there.

435
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:07,685
Don't shut the door, Ali's coming up

436
00:31:07,715 --> 00:31:08,680
Don't shut the door, Ali's coming up.

437
00:31:08,710 --> 00:31:09,120
Sure

438
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:17,240
Come on, lie down.

439
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:25,800
Take my sleeve, hold this bit.

440
00:31:28,480 --> 00:31:29,400
Thanks

441
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:38,360
Wait, let me take off your scarf.

442
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:41,640
You want me to put
two pillows for you?

443
00:31:41,670 --> 00:31:42,560
No.

444
00:31:50,760 --> 00:31:52,920
Turn off the light, so she can sleep.

445
00:31:53,120 --> 00:31:53,880
Don't turn it off.

446
00:31:55,640 --> 00:31:57,080
Can I get you anything?

447
00:31:57,880 --> 00:31:58,120
No, thanks.

448
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:08,040
Where are you going, Emad?

449
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:10,290
Darling?

450
00:32:10,320 --> 00:32:11,770
I said, where are you going?

451
00:32:11,800 --> 00:32:14,640
I'm not going anywhere,
I'll be here. Do you need anything?

452
00:32:14,670 --> 00:32:18,360
Nope. Leave the door open.

453
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:28,920
Okay, thanks

454
00:32:29,560 --> 00:32:31,440
Look, her blood pressure's low,
be careful when she's walking around.

455
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:33,080
Thanks for everything.

456
00:32:34,200 --> 00:32:35,920
Sit down guys,
I'll make you some breakfast.

457
00:32:35,950 --> 00:32:36,880
No thanks, I'm fine.

458
00:32:37,920 --> 00:32:40,600
Come on, you haven't eaten
since last night.

459
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:46,280
Kati, you wanna stay here, and
make soup or something for them?

460
00:32:46,281 --> 00:32:47,381
- You want me to stay?
- You want Kati to stay?

461
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:48,120
No, no.

462
00:32:48,480 --> 00:32:49,360
Are you sure?

463
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:52,120
You must be tired.
Go, get some rest.

464
00:32:52,840 --> 00:32:53,680
Call if you need anything.

465
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:57,250
Really, man, just let us know.

466
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:59,280
- Thanks again for everything, guys.
- Bye

467
00:35:02,440 --> 00:35:07,795
<i>... scrap metal... Iron doors...
Aluminium doors...</i>

468
00:35:07,825 --> 00:35:11,680
<i>Fences... Metal dishes...
buying...</i>

469
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:23,840
<i>... scrap metal... lamps...Samovars...
anything, bring it over...</i>

470
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:49,080
Come on, stand here
while I use the bathroom.

471
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:03,770
What are you doing?

472
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:06,320
Leave it, I'll wash it myself,
Rana, dear. Leave it.

473
00:37:06,680 --> 00:37:07,580
Come and wash it then.

474
00:37:07,600 --> 00:37:08,920
Alright, turn off the water
and come out.

475
00:37:12,720 --> 00:37:14,760
Then, come and clean it
before I use it.

476
00:37:15,480 --> 00:37:17,560
The police might need to see it.

477
00:37:22,200 --> 00:37:22,880
Yes?

478
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:26,240
Of course, sorry

479
00:37:26,440 --> 00:37:27,280
Who was it?

480
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:28,920
A neighbor

481
00:37:29,280 --> 00:37:29,840
What did they say?

482
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:30,680
I'll be right back.

483
00:37:36,680 --> 00:37:38,000
Sorry

484
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:53,600
I'm really sorry for all the trouble
you've been put through, ma'am.

485
00:37:53,630 --> 00:37:56,260
Now, come on, don't say that.

486
00:37:56,261 --> 00:37:59,061
I think you should call 110, they'll be
able to track him down through the car.

487
00:37:59,160 --> 00:38:02,560
Yeah, I'll definitely do that.
Anyways, I'll try to find some place...

488
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:05,480
Here I was thinking, when that woman left
she's taken all her troubles with her.

489
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:08,240
Have you ever seen
this car's owner around here?

490
00:38:08,680 --> 00:38:12,045
Well, it wasn't like, just
a couple guys visiting her.

491
00:38:12,075 --> 00:38:15,440
I might have to trouble you again
when the police comes...

492
00:38:15,441 --> 00:38:17,541
...if they have any questions
about exactly what you saw.

493
00:38:17,580 --> 00:38:19,960
Of course, it's our duty. Would you
like to take my mobile number?

494
00:38:19,990 --> 00:38:20,980
Yes, please.

495
00:38:21,010 --> 00:38:21,970
I'll get going.

496
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:23,220
Thank you so much, ma'am.

497
00:38:23,920 --> 00:38:25,905
They should put an ewer
around these guys necks,

498
00:38:25,935 --> 00:38:27,920
and parade them around the city,
shaming them.

499
00:38:27,950 --> 00:38:29,720
0912...

500
00:38:48,120 --> 00:38:49,970
Why are you out here? Come in

501
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:52,240
I'm scared of being
alone in the house.

502
00:38:53,640 --> 00:38:54,840
Where did you go?

503
00:38:56,840 --> 00:38:59,600
I went to thank the neighbors
for last night.

504
00:39:00,360 --> 00:39:01,440
What did they say?

505
00:39:01,470 --> 00:39:02,740
Nothing.

506
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:04,370
They asked how you were.

507
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:07,960
You didn't tell Kati and the guys
what happened, did you?

508
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:09,200
No.

509
00:39:10,080 --> 00:39:11,720
Okay, I'm going to
the police station.

510
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:15,400
We have to file a complaint
for them to start looking for the guy.

511
00:39:15,720 --> 00:39:17,565
How will they find him?

512
00:39:17,595 --> 00:39:19,410
He left his pickup behind.

513
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:23,480
His mobile too,
but it's disconnected.

514
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:27,280
Who was he, Emad?

515
00:39:30,080 --> 00:39:33,840
The neighbors are saying the woman
who lived here before us was shady.

516
00:39:34,520 --> 00:39:38,440
The scumbag must've been
one of her customers.

517
00:39:38,441 --> 00:39:39,641
Came here on account of her.

518
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:43,440
Do you remember what he looked like?

519
00:39:43,960 --> 00:39:45,160
No

520
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:47,500
Didn't you get a look at him?

521
00:39:56,080 --> 00:39:58,180
It's cold.
Come inside, you'll catch a cold.

522
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:12,800
Gimme that.

523
00:40:19,280 --> 00:40:21,400
Who helped me out of the bathroom?

524
00:40:23,360 --> 00:40:25,040
One of the neighbors.

525
00:40:25,240 --> 00:40:26,590
Which one?

526
00:40:26,620 --> 00:40:28,800
I don't know, just forget it.

527
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:36,160
Eat your breakfast.
and then go get some rest.

528
00:40:38,880 --> 00:40:43,440
I can't. As soon as I close my eyes
that scene comes to my mind.

529
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:54,400
How did he get in?

530
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:59,480
I opened the door,
I thought it was you.

531
00:41:00,400 --> 00:41:05,000
I came out of the bathroom,
buzzed him in, and then went back.

532
00:41:12,200 --> 00:41:16,000
I was shampooing my hair when
I realised someone had come in.

533
00:41:17,480 --> 00:41:20,720
He put his hand in my hair from behind
and I thought it was you.

534
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:25,260
But then I saw his hands
and after that it's blank.

535
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:41,720
Rana...

536
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:45,440
Darling, have some breakfast.

537
00:41:51,160 --> 00:41:52,280
Rana, dear...

538
00:41:54,480 --> 00:41:55,640
Sweetie...

539
00:42:51,680 --> 00:42:53,440
What about tonight's performance?

540
00:42:54,640 --> 00:42:56,640
I called and told them to cancel it.

541
00:42:56,840 --> 00:42:57,505
No, call and say I'm coming.

542
00:42:57,535 --> 00:42:58,200
How? In this condition of yours?

543
00:42:59,960 --> 00:43:02,020
It's harder for me to stay at home.

544
00:43:07,640 --> 00:43:09,540
Put this on,
let's go to the police station.

545
00:43:09,570 --> 00:43:11,600
We might get held up there
for a while anyways.

546
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:13,500
No, leave it.
Let's not go to the station.

547
00:43:13,840 --> 00:43:15,200
We can't just do nothing!

548
00:43:16,880 --> 00:43:19,497
I don't want to have
to go there and tell

549
00:43:19,527 --> 00:43:22,400
a bunch of officers or
whoever what happened.

550
00:43:23,120 --> 00:43:25,920
Did something happen
that you can't tell?

551
00:43:27,120 --> 00:43:28,010
No.

552
00:43:28,040 --> 00:43:30,800
Then, you don't have to say anything.
I'll tell 'em myself.

553
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:33,400
I can't, it'll be too much.

554
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:46,000
No, this isn't foolish talk, Linda.

555
00:43:46,280 --> 00:43:50,080
When I'm walking in the street,
I clearly feel these things...

556
00:43:50,181 --> 00:43:54,581
...They pass me by, but it's as if they're
laughing at me with their eyes.

557
00:43:54,680 --> 00:43:58,160
Why? Why would they laugh at you?
Don't talk that way about yourself, Willy.

558
00:43:58,920 --> 00:44:01,440
Sometimes they pass me by
as if I don't even exist.

559
00:44:02,520 --> 00:44:06,680
As though nobody sees me.
Nobody notices me. Nothing.

560
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:13,240
Linda?

561
00:44:20,840 --> 00:44:25,520
How long are you going to spend
repairing those socks, huh?

562
00:44:26,040 --> 00:44:28,200
You know it makes me angry.

563
00:44:28,201 --> 00:44:32,201
At least don't do it while I'm home,
talking to you. Okay?

564
00:44:37,460 --> 00:44:43,760
Okay, we'll talk about something else,
for example my income.

565
00:44:44,320 --> 00:44:50,400
My never-changing income.
God, this is really ridiculous.

566
00:44:50,540 --> 00:44:51,493
<i>What's wrong with you?..</i>

567
00:44:51,523 --> 00:44:52,780
<i>why aren't you saying your lines?</i>

568
00:44:52,880 --> 00:44:58,160
Willy, darling, you're the most
handsome man in the world to me.

569
00:45:01,600 --> 00:45:06,800
You always say this to me, Linda, always,
but it doesn't help me at all.

570
00:45:06,830 --> 00:45:09,130
I'll never be able to make you happy,
do you know why?

571
00:45:09,160 --> 00:45:13,400
Because I'm just a salesman.
I'm nothing! I'm nothing, Linda!

572
00:45:13,520 --> 00:45:18,080
But I always tried...
why are you crying, anyways?

573
00:45:21,960 --> 00:45:23,480
Wait, where are you going?

574
00:45:24,440 --> 00:45:25,960
Linda, come back...

575
00:45:31,280 --> 00:45:35,760
Sorry, I have to stop the play.
I apologize to you all.

576
00:45:36,120 --> 00:45:39,172
My wife, the other actor,
isn't feeling well.

577
00:45:39,202 --> 00:45:42,600
Please give us a ten minute intermission.
Sorry.

578
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:47,490
Can you carry on?

579
00:45:47,520 --> 00:45:48,811
What do you mean, Kati?

580
00:45:48,841 --> 00:45:51,480
Can't you see she's not well?
Go on, cancel it.

581
00:45:51,560 --> 00:45:54,320
Do you wanna go to the other room
and lie down a little?

582
00:45:54,520 --> 00:45:58,080
Alright, guys, let's just clear the room.
She's not well.

583
00:46:00,400 --> 00:46:02,245
Sanam, dear.

584
00:46:02,275 --> 00:46:04,090
I'm coming.

585
00:46:04,120 --> 00:46:06,120
Can I get you anything?

586
00:46:11,760 --> 00:46:13,000
Kati darling...

587
00:46:13,440 --> 00:46:15,360
Go and cancel the show

588
00:46:25,360 --> 00:46:27,360
What happened there?

589
00:46:31,280 --> 00:46:35,280
The way someone in the audience
was staring at me bothered me.

590
00:46:37,960 --> 00:46:41,760
The audience've come to watch the play,
of course they'll be looking at you.

591
00:46:41,800 --> 00:46:44,280
Looked at me just like that guy.

592
00:46:50,040 --> 00:46:51,970
I thought you said you didn't see him.

593
00:46:52,000 --> 00:46:56,200
I'm really unwell, I just
don't know what to do.

594
00:46:59,200 --> 00:47:00,880
Babak, come here a minute.

595
00:47:00,910 --> 00:47:02,400
Coming...

596
00:47:10,600 --> 00:47:12,400
Is she feeling better?

597
00:47:13,160 --> 00:47:15,900
Goddamit, man,
what can I say to you...?

598
00:47:15,901 --> 00:47:17,765
Don't you think you had
to let me know about

599
00:47:17,795 --> 00:47:19,701
the kind of people who
used to live in there?

600
00:47:19,860 --> 00:47:21,490
- What's happened?
- You're supposed to be my friend

601
00:47:21,520 --> 00:47:25,400
Seriously, what's happened?
What is it to you who lived there before?

602
00:47:25,640 --> 00:47:28,400
That apartment's infamous
in the whole neighborhood.

603
00:47:28,720 --> 00:47:29,980
Who's said such a thing?

604
00:47:30,080 --> 00:47:31,581
Let's say nobody's said anything,

605
00:47:31,611 --> 00:47:33,840
why isn't this woman coming
to collect her stuff?

606
00:47:33,870 --> 00:47:36,820
I just wanted to help.

607
00:47:36,821 --> 00:47:40,321
Remember the state you were in, last week?
Ready to sleep on the set?

608
00:47:40,420 --> 00:47:43,300
Regardless, should you have hidden
that woman's line of work from me?

609
00:47:43,480 --> 00:47:44,340
What hiding?

610
00:47:44,480 --> 00:47:47,060
Well, yeah. Did you tell me or not?

611
00:47:47,180 --> 00:47:52,680
Was I supposed to pass on to you some
unfounded gossip? To upset you?

612
00:47:52,710 --> 00:47:54,920
Well, what's going, anyways?
What's this all about?

613
00:47:54,950 --> 00:47:56,320
Babak, I'm going

614
00:47:56,350 --> 00:47:56,960
I'm coming.

615
00:47:57,160 --> 00:48:00,240
Go take a look at Rana,
you'll see what this is all about.

616
00:48:00,320 --> 00:48:02,680
They said she slipped
in the bathroom.

617
00:48:05,800 --> 00:48:09,160
We said right in front of you
we might be having a kid in that place.

618
00:48:09,261 --> 00:48:10,761
And you didn't say a word, what kind of...

619
00:48:10,960 --> 00:48:13,040
You were joking!

620
00:48:13,680 --> 00:48:16,360
If we weren't joking,
would you have told us?

621
00:48:16,390 --> 00:48:19,490
Told you what?!

622
00:48:19,520 --> 00:48:22,380
Put yourself in my shoes,
the same room we sleep in, each night...

623
00:48:22,381 --> 00:48:26,881
...how many strange men
have been with that woman.

624
00:48:26,960 --> 00:48:31,600
Don't take it so hard on yourself.
I haven't cashed your check yet.

625
00:48:31,630 --> 00:48:35,587
Whenever you find another
place whose previous tenants

626
00:48:35,617 --> 00:48:38,400
had your approval,
you can move out.

627
00:48:49,520 --> 00:48:50,010
Hello

628
00:48:50,040 --> 00:48:50,440
Hello
Hello

629
00:48:50,470 --> 00:48:50,810
Hello

630
00:48:50,840 --> 00:48:51,560
How are you doing

631
00:48:51,720 --> 00:48:56,530
Be careful not to slip on the
stairs Mrs Shahnazari, they're wet.

632
00:48:56,560 --> 00:49:02,345
I was actually going to ask the cleaner
to come early and sort these out.

633
00:49:02,375 --> 00:49:08,160
But, I thought you'd want to report it,
the police might want to see them.

634
00:49:08,190 --> 00:49:10,880
Well, it wasn't such a big deal.

635
00:49:11,160 --> 00:49:14,591
You wouldn't say that,
if you'd been there and seen

636
00:49:14,621 --> 00:49:18,120
the state your wife was in,
on the bathroom floor.

637
00:49:18,840 --> 00:49:26,000
When Mr. Alimoradi opened the bathroom door,
he thought, God forbid, your wife was dead.

638
00:49:26,030 --> 00:49:28,800
Say hello from me.

639
00:49:34,440 --> 00:49:36,080
Get up, I've made some breakfast for you.

640
00:49:36,320 --> 00:49:37,360
I'm heading out.

641
00:49:37,390 --> 00:49:38,120
Wait.

642
00:49:43,960 --> 00:49:46,360
Wait, I'll get ready and come with you.

643
00:49:46,390 --> 00:49:48,320
Where to? I have class.

644
00:49:48,400 --> 00:49:50,080
I know, I'll wait in the car.

645
00:49:50,360 --> 00:49:52,920
It's not just an hour or two,
you'll get tired.

646
00:49:53,120 --> 00:49:54,480
Then don't go today.

647
00:49:54,500 --> 00:49:55,250
What?

648
00:49:55,280 --> 00:49:57,600
I said, don't go today.

649
00:49:57,920 --> 00:50:00,485
Let's say I don't,
what about tomorrow then?

650
00:50:00,515 --> 00:50:03,080
The day after tomorrow?
It's not gonna work.

651
00:50:03,110 --> 00:50:05,800
I can't stay here alone.

652
00:50:06,800 --> 00:50:09,680
I said, I don't want
to be here alone.

653
00:50:10,040 --> 00:50:13,022
What can I do?
You want me to get you

654
00:50:13,052 --> 00:50:16,760
a ticket to visit your
parents for a few days?

655
00:50:17,440 --> 00:50:19,000
Looking like this?

656
00:50:20,480 --> 00:50:22,100
I've made up my mind...

657
00:50:22,101 --> 00:50:27,201
... we either have to go to the police,
or forget this altogether.

658
00:50:27,300 --> 00:50:30,760
Okay forget it,but let's look for
a new apartment right from today.

659
00:50:30,790 --> 00:50:32,210
Okay, we'll start looking.

660
00:50:32,240 --> 00:50:36,080
But until we find somewhere,
you need to try and pick yourself up.

661
00:50:36,110 --> 00:50:38,032
What do you mean?
It's not something I can control.

662
00:50:38,062 --> 00:50:39,985
You taking your pills and
not staying up all night

663
00:50:40,015 --> 00:50:42,080
getting worked up about it,
is up to you, isn't it?

664
00:50:42,480 --> 00:50:46,640
Go take a shower, I'll wait here.

665
00:50:47,960 --> 00:50:49,880
I don't want to go in that bathroom.

666
00:50:53,800 --> 00:50:55,720
I'll drop you off at a friend's place.
Use theirs.

667
00:50:55,750 --> 00:50:58,400
Go and tell them we've
come to take a shower?

668
00:50:58,620 --> 00:51:01,140
What do you want me to do?

669
00:51:02,840 --> 00:51:04,760
You keep changing your mind.

670
00:51:05,440 --> 00:51:07,678
At night you tell me
not to come near you,

671
00:51:07,708 --> 00:51:10,320
then in the morning you
tell me not to leave you.

672
00:51:10,350 --> 00:51:12,240
Tell me what to do and I'll do it.

673
00:51:12,270 --> 00:51:12,850
Just go, you're late

674
00:51:12,880 --> 00:51:15,986
It'll take a couple weeks to find a place.
What?

675
00:51:16,016 --> 00:51:19,320
You're not gonna wash up
with that wound of yours?

676
00:51:37,760 --> 00:51:39,800
I love you.

677
00:51:42,040 --> 00:51:44,770
Just think, it could've been worse.

678
00:51:44,800 --> 00:51:47,329
What if a piece of glass
had gone in your eye,

679
00:51:47,359 --> 00:51:49,544
or your head had been hit harder?
Then...

680
00:51:49,574 --> 00:51:51,760
...then what the hell would I have done?

681
00:51:52,280 --> 00:51:54,240
I wish my head had been hit harder.

682
00:51:56,080 --> 00:51:59,160
God forbid! Honey,
don't say things like that.

683
00:52:58,520 --> 00:53:00,480
Hello, Mr. Etesami.

684
00:53:12,560 --> 00:53:15,320
Hello Sir, how are you doing?

685
00:53:15,960 --> 00:53:18,360
Mr. Yeganeh gave me these books
to give them to you.

686
00:53:19,280 --> 00:53:21,760
Be quiet. What's so funny?

687
00:53:24,200 --> 00:53:25,290
Why?

688
00:53:25,320 --> 00:53:27,840
He said they're not suitable for kids.

689
00:53:28,560 --> 00:53:30,280
Quiet!

690
00:53:31,560 --> 00:53:34,520
Mr. Yeganeh decided these
weren't suitable for the kids?!

691
00:53:35,920 --> 00:53:37,720
Go, throw them in the bin.

692
00:53:37,920 --> 00:53:38,610
Why the bin?

693
00:53:38,640 --> 00:53:40,640
Just throw them away.

694
00:53:51,640 --> 00:53:52,730
Give me your phone.

695
00:53:52,760 --> 00:53:54,040
I don't have a phone, Sir.

696
00:53:54,070 --> 00:53:54,730
Give it to me.

697
00:53:54,760 --> 00:53:55,880
I don't have a cell.

698
00:53:56,440 --> 00:53:58,080
Sir, wait a minute.

699
00:54:01,560 --> 00:54:02,410
Give it to me.

700
00:54:02,440 --> 00:54:03,740
Sir, there's nothing in it about you.

701
00:54:04,040 --> 00:54:04,840
I want to see what you have

702
00:54:04,870 --> 00:54:05,980
I've deleted it

703
00:54:06,010 --> 00:54:07,090
Let me see it

704
00:54:07,120 --> 00:54:08,890
Sir please, I've deleted it

705
00:54:08,920 --> 00:54:11,960
Sir, I have private photos in there

706
00:54:12,200 --> 00:54:13,425
Put your hand down

707
00:54:13,455 --> 00:54:14,680
That's not fair

708
00:54:16,360 --> 00:54:17,680
Mr Etesami?

709
00:54:19,200 --> 00:54:20,600
Sir?

710
00:54:22,200 --> 00:54:26,200
I have personal things on there.
I deleted the video.

711
00:54:28,200 --> 00:54:30,400
On my mother's life, I deleted it

712
00:54:30,640 --> 00:54:33,051
Sir, send it on Telegram,
so that everyone can see.

713
00:54:33,081 --> 00:54:34,690
It's much better than this movie.

714
00:54:34,720 --> 00:54:37,600
I'll kick you out of the class,
if you say another word.

715
00:54:38,080 --> 00:54:38,825
Mr. Etesami!

716
00:54:38,855 --> 00:54:39,570
Sorry, Sir

717
00:54:39,600 --> 00:54:40,480
You stay out of this!

718
00:54:40,510 --> 00:54:41,330
Mr Etesami?

719
00:54:41,360 --> 00:54:43,340
I mean all of you.

720
00:54:43,341 --> 00:54:44,841
I'm talking to him.

721
00:54:45,320 --> 00:54:46,800
I deleted it

722
00:54:47,720 --> 00:54:48,800
Please

723
00:54:52,480 --> 00:54:54,004
Call your father to
come to the school

724
00:54:54,034 --> 00:54:56,000
and see the kind of photos
you have on your cell.

725
00:54:57,840 --> 00:54:59,920
His dad's dead, Sir.

726
00:55:53,240 --> 00:55:54,800
Hi, sorry about that

727
00:55:54,830 --> 00:55:57,380
Hi, no problem.

728
00:55:57,381 --> 00:56:01,381
If it's a hassle for you to keep moving it,
then you can leave it in the corner.

729
00:56:01,411 --> 00:56:01,530
Next to the boiler room.

730
00:56:01,560 --> 00:56:04,925
When my husband gets back
he'll move it to a better place.

731
00:56:04,955 --> 00:56:08,320
I don't want you to have to keep
going up and down the stairs.

732
00:56:08,350 --> 00:56:11,560
I'm going out for a couple of hours
you can take my spot.

733
00:56:11,590 --> 00:56:13,600
Don't worry,
I'll find a better place for it.

734
00:56:13,630 --> 00:56:15,120
Suit yourself.

735
00:56:15,150 --> 00:56:15,370
Sorry

736
00:56:15,400 --> 00:56:17,960
If you give me the keys, I can do it

737
00:56:17,990 --> 00:56:18,640
Thanks

738
00:56:20,920 --> 00:56:24,720
My wife said, you're not going to report it.

739
00:56:24,750 --> 00:56:25,330
No.

740
00:56:25,360 --> 00:56:26,615
You're doing the right thing,

741
00:56:26,645 --> 00:56:28,650
they won't do anything,
even if they catch him.

742
00:56:28,680 --> 00:56:34,320
And you'll have to explain over and over
why you opened the door

743
00:56:34,321 --> 00:56:36,721
... plus trekking back
and forth to the court.

744
00:56:36,820 --> 00:56:38,610
Endless hassle for nothing

745
00:56:38,640 --> 00:56:43,040
But he'll probably be back for his car.
Please, call me if he shows up.

746
00:56:43,070 --> 00:56:45,040
I'll sort out that bastard.

747
00:56:58,120 --> 00:57:01,680
I'll take mine out and
then come and park yours.

748
00:57:01,710 --> 00:57:03,440
There's no need,
I'll do it myself.

749
00:57:03,470 --> 00:57:04,920
Okay, then, goodbye.
Thanks.

750
00:57:05,600 --> 00:57:07,240
Goodbye

751
00:57:35,120 --> 00:57:35,890
How's it going?

752
00:57:35,920 --> 00:57:38,280
Hey, you okay?
Is Rana here?

753
00:57:38,310 --> 00:57:39,540
No, wasn't she with you?

754
00:57:39,570 --> 00:57:41,070
She's coming on her own

755
00:57:41,100 --> 00:57:42,600
Any news about the guy?

756
00:57:46,040 --> 00:57:47,520
Who?

757
00:57:48,800 --> 00:57:51,640
Babak had heard some things
from your neighbors.

758
00:57:54,440 --> 00:57:56,000
Where is he?
Is he here?

759
00:57:56,030 --> 00:57:57,050
Babak?

760
00:57:57,080 --> 00:57:58,840
Yep, he's back there.

761
00:58:06,080 --> 00:58:07,280
Hi

762
00:58:07,400 --> 00:58:08,170
Hi

763
00:58:08,200 --> 00:58:09,880
Why didn't you tell me yesterday?

764
00:58:11,200 --> 00:58:12,490
What should I have told you?

765
00:58:12,520 --> 00:58:14,640
About the man turning up
the other night.

766
00:58:15,960 --> 00:58:17,560
How's Rana?

767
00:58:18,080 --> 00:58:19,840
The neighbors told you

768
00:58:22,080 --> 00:58:24,130
They're also worried...

769
00:58:24,160 --> 00:58:26,360
Tell 'em nothing happened,
the guy just barged in.

770
00:58:26,390 --> 00:58:28,440
Then why are you keeping his pickup?

771
00:58:28,470 --> 00:58:30,520
Shahnazari said it's in the parking lot.

772
00:58:30,840 --> 00:58:35,720
Tell them we'll be gone soon
