01:12:54,800 --> 01:12:57,890
It was a pickup, if I give you
the number plate...

1019
01:12:57,920 --> 01:13:01,880
Can your Dad find the guy's address?
If it's not too much trouble, that is.

1020
01:13:01,910 --> 01:13:03,739
Sure,
he has contacts in the department.

1021
01:13:03,769 --> 01:13:06,000
If you gimme the license plate,
he can find out.

1022
01:13:06,030 --> 01:13:08,010
But, I think you should report it.

1023
01:13:08,040 --> 01:13:11,960
It wasn't anything serious, so
I don't wanna get the police mixed up.

1024
01:13:11,990 --> 01:13:14,520
Okay, gimme the registration
and I'll call my Dad.

1025
01:13:15,732 --> 01:13:17,432
- Get a pen and a paper, then.
- Okay.

1026
01:13:23,622 --> 01:13:24,822
Why don’t you want to work for me?

1027
01:13:25,123 --> 01:13:27,123
Have you lost your mind, Charlie?
I've got a job.

1028
01:13:27,924 --> 01:13:30,324
Then what’re you walkin’
in here every week for?

1029
01:13:35,125 --> 01:13:37,225
Well, if you don’t want me to
walk in here...

1030
01:13:37,626 --> 01:13:38,997
I'm offering you a job.

1031
01:13:39,027 --> 01:13:43,427
I don't want your goddam job!
I've got one already. Get outa my way!

1032
01:13:43,528 --> 01:13:45,928
When the hell are you
going to grow up, huh?

1033
01:13:46,329 --> 01:13:48,929
Goddam you, Charlie!
You big ignoramus!

1034
01:13:49,030 --> 01:13:53,730
Big ignoramus!
How dare you talk to me like that?

1035
01:13:53,831 --> 01:13:56,931
If you say that to me again,
I’II rap you one!

1036
01:13:59,932 --> 01:14:01,432
I don’t care how big you are!

1037
01:14:01,933 --> 01:14:04,133
You degenerate!

1038
01:14:16,933 --> 01:14:18,633
What's wrong with you tonight?

1039
01:14:19,334 --> 01:14:20,134
What did I do?

1040
01:14:20,235 --> 01:14:21,735
Why are you adding dialogues?

1041
01:14:22,336 --> 01:14:23,036
What did I add?

1042
01:14:23,737 --> 01:14:25,937
If you've got a problem with me,
let's sit and talk.

1043
01:14:26,138 --> 01:14:28,538
Not on the stage, calling me,
"You degenerate!"

1044
01:14:28,539 --> 01:14:31,039
It's neither improvisation, nor acting,
you're insulting me.

1045
01:14:31,140 --> 01:14:32,740
What?
Did I hurt your feeling?

1046
01:14:32,741 --> 01:14:34,041
Yeah.

1047
01:14:34,542 --> 01:14:37,142
And if you do that one more time,
I'll answer you right in front of everyone.

1048
01:14:37,543 --> 01:14:40,043
Degenerate is the one who speaks his mind
through swearing.

1049
01:14:40,244 --> 01:14:41,044
Didn't know that.

1050
01:14:41,945 --> 01:14:43,145
I'm really sorry.

1051
01:14:59,145 --> 01:15:01,045
Bakery

1052
01:15:09,646 --> 01:15:10,746
Hello, how're you doing?

1053
01:15:18,947 --> 01:15:24,047
<i>Speaking Azeri</i>

1054
01:15:34,248 --> 01:15:35,648
What can I do for you?

1055
01:15:36,749 --> 01:15:37,549
Two baguettes, please.

1056
01:15:41,450 --> 01:15:43,450
You want 'em cut?
Thanks a lot.

1057
01:15:44,151 --> 01:15:46,551
That pickup is yours?
Why?

1058
01:15:46,852 --> 01:15:49,352
There's an officer writing tickets,
from the top of the street.

1059
01:15:50,053 --> 01:15:52,153
Majid, come here, go move the car.

1060
01:15:52,554 --> 01:15:54,754
...before the officer slaps a ticket on it.

1061
01:16:05,155 --> 01:16:06,555
Soheil, bring the keys.

1062
01:16:11,156 --> 01:16:12,056
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

1063
01:16:12,957 --> 01:16:14,057
Later.

1064
01:16:14,758 --> 01:16:15,558
Bye.

1065
01:16:16,159 --> 01:16:17,559
Here you go, Sir.

1066
01:16:17,660 --> 01:16:18,760
Thanks.

1067
01:16:59,461 --> 01:17:01,961
Thanks, dude.
I'll take a water.

1068
01:17:03,462 --> 01:17:05,162
Hello, mister, sorry
is that your pickup?

1069
01:17:05,763 --> 01:17:06,563
Yeah.

1070
01:17:06,864 --> 01:17:09,364
I had some load, I wanted to
ask you to move it for me.

1071
01:17:09,565 --> 01:17:10,765
Nah, that pickup is for a store.

1072
01:17:11,266 --> 01:17:12,566
Well, not now, whenever you're free.

1073
01:17:12,967 --> 01:17:14,867
No, it's just that, I do something else.
I don't do that.

1074
01:17:15,368 --> 01:17:16,768
Not even Friday?

1075
01:17:16,869 --> 01:17:17,089
Nah.

1076
01:17:17,119 --> 01:17:19,869
You can find pickups at
the top of Haft-e-Tir.

1077
01:17:20,170 --> 01:17:22,019
No, it's just that,
my stuff are books and paintings

1078
01:17:22,049 --> 01:17:23,970
and things like that,
I was looking for a softopper.

1079
01:17:24,071 --> 01:17:27,171
You know, on account of rain
or things like that.

1080
01:17:27,572 --> 01:17:28,972
I'm really busy.
I don't have time.

1081
01:17:29,273 --> 01:17:32,373
I don't care about the fee. I'll pay.
I just want my stuff to get there safe.

1082
01:17:32,474 --> 01:17:34,374
It's just that, I'm busy.
I can't.

1083
01:17:34,575 --> 01:17:36,875
Majid, come on, man.
Help the guy. Late night or something.

1084
01:17:37,676 --> 01:17:40,676
Well, how about you gimme your number?
I'll call you whenever you say.

1085
01:17:40,777 --> 01:17:43,077
And if you come yourself,
even better.

1086
01:17:43,178 --> 01:17:45,378
Bro, find some time between
your schedule for him.

1087
01:17:48,179 --> 01:17:50,079
Careful not to hit the walls.

1088
01:17:55,180 --> 01:17:57,580
Ah! what're you doing here?

1089
01:17:58,781 --> 01:18:00,781
Come here... kitty...

1090
01:18:04,782 --> 01:18:06,182
Careful with that not to scratch it.

1091
01:18:07,183 --> 01:18:09,483
Babak, tell 'em to come
have a cup of tea.

1092
01:18:10,084 --> 01:18:11,984
- There's no need for that.
- It's getting cold.

1093
01:18:16,085 --> 01:18:17,885
Where are you taking these?

1094
01:18:17,986 --> 01:18:21,786
I'm taking'em to my parent's parking lot.
We'll see what happens.

1095
01:18:21,987 --> 01:18:23,187
Won't she come to take 'em?

1096
01:18:23,888 --> 01:18:26,588
She's got problems of her own.
She hasn't found a place yet.

1097
01:18:33,590 --> 01:18:35,990
Get up, Babak wants to
take away that woman's stuff.

1098
01:18:36,791 --> 01:18:37,891
What do you want me to do?

1099
01:18:42,192 --> 01:18:43,792
What's going on
between you two?

1100
01:18:44,093 --> 01:18:45,893
Nothing, let him take 'em.
That's okay with me.

1101
01:18:53,494 --> 01:18:55,794
Hello? Majid?

1102
01:18:56,695 --> 01:18:58,495
It's me, Etesami, couple days ago.

1103
01:18:58,696 --> 01:19:00,396
You free today?

1104
01:19:01,297 --> 01:19:02,297
How about Friday?

1105
01:20:06,797 --> 01:20:07,897
Yeah?

1106
01:20:09,698 --> 01:20:10,398
You?

1107
01:20:12,999 --> 01:20:14,899
Yeah, come on up.

1108
01:20:35,198 --> 01:20:36,598
Hello, can I help you?

1109
01:20:36,999 --> 01:20:39,999
Hello, Sir. You okay?
Have I come to the right place?

1110
01:20:40,300 --> 01:20:42,000
Majid said, there's some stuff
you need to move.

1111
01:20:42,581 --> 01:20:44,701
That's right, come on in.
Why didn't he come himself?

1112
01:20:44,802 --> 01:20:47,702
Well, he was busy,
so he sent me instead.

1113
01:20:49,703 --> 01:20:50,703
- After you.
- You first.

1114
01:20:50,804 --> 01:20:52,804
But he didn't say anything
about all these stairs.

1115
01:20:54,005 --> 01:20:55,305
With this heart of mine.

1116
01:20:55,405 --> 01:20:56,780
Well, if I knew you're coming,

1117
01:20:56,810 --> 01:20:59,605
I would've told him about the stairs,
and the broken elevator.

1118
01:20:59,906 --> 01:21:03,906
Well, I can't use elevators anyways, Sir.
Would you gimme a glass of water?

1119
01:21:09,107 --> 01:21:10,207
Have you hired movers?

1120
01:21:10,907 --> 01:21:15,007
No, I thought he's coming.
And, we'd take the boxes ourselves.

1121
01:21:15,108 --> 01:21:17,008
Well, the poor guy
was kinda busy today.

1122
01:21:18,309 --> 01:21:20,109
- Is he your son?
- Nah, my son-in-law.

1123
01:21:20,210 --> 01:21:22,410
Doesn't make a difference though.
He's like my own son.

1124
01:21:30,311 --> 01:21:34,411
Sorry, old man, we just moved out.
There's no glasses or anything.

1125
01:21:34,712 --> 01:21:36,512
That's alright, mister.
I'll drink from the tap.

1126
01:21:38,613 --> 01:21:39,813
Where are the boxes?

1127
01:21:41,014 --> 01:21:42,114
In that room.

1128
01:21:42,815 --> 01:21:44,915
We'll see. If there's too many,
we'll call movers.

1129
01:21:47,916 --> 01:21:51,816
Give him a call. Maybe he's around
here somewhere. I can pick him up.

1130
01:21:52,917 --> 01:21:53,917
Who?

1131
01:21:54,317 --> 01:21:55,117
Your son-in-law.

1132
01:21:55,818 --> 01:21:59,518
Nah, the poor souls just went shopping
for the "exchange of the vows" ceremony.

1133
01:22:04,419 --> 01:22:06,319
Isn't the janitor
allowed to help here?

1134
01:22:06,920 --> 01:22:08,520
Nah, the building's empty.

1135
01:22:08,621 --> 01:22:10,921
The walls caved,
the residents have all moved out.

1136
01:22:11,022 --> 01:22:13,622
Wow, wow! what if it collapses
on us or something?

1137
01:22:13,923 --> 01:22:14,723
Nah.

1138
01:22:14,924 --> 01:22:17,824
Let's take a look and see
if it's worth hiring movers.

1139
01:22:18,925 --> 01:22:19,725
Grandpa!

1140
01:22:20,626 --> 01:22:21,326
What?

1141
01:22:21,627 --> 01:22:24,727
Would you come sit here for a sec?
I wanna tell you something.

1142
01:22:24,828 --> 01:22:26,728
Look here, mister,
this isn't my line of work.

1143
01:22:26,729 --> 01:22:28,929
Majid, said, "there's this guy,
who's called a couple times...

1144
01:22:28,930 --> 01:22:31,830
...would you do it?"
I said, okay, why not?

1145
01:22:31,831 --> 01:22:33,731
Now, you paying depends on
how generous you're feeling.

1146
01:22:33,732 --> 01:22:37,732
Nah, it's not about... wages,
fees, and stuff like that.

1147
01:22:38,333 --> 01:22:41,133
Just sit down. There's something
I have to tell you.

1148
01:22:44,134 --> 01:22:46,034
Good news, I hope.

1149
01:22:49,635 --> 01:22:51,235
How long do you know this guy?

1150
01:22:51,936 --> 01:22:53,636
- My son-in-law?
- Yeah.

1151
01:22:53,937 --> 01:22:54,637
What for?

1152
01:22:54,938 --> 01:22:56,238
I wanna know
if you know him well.

1153
01:22:57,039 --> 01:22:59,339
Well, it's about two years they've
asked for my daughter's hand.

1154
01:23:00,340 --> 01:23:02,040
Have you asked around
about him?

1155
01:23:04,741 --> 01:23:06,141
Do you know Majid?

1156
01:23:07,742 --> 01:23:09,642
If there's anything you know,
just tell me.

1157
01:23:10,843 --> 01:23:14,743
When my wife and I moved out of here,
we went to a place that...

1158
01:23:15,944 --> 01:23:21,744
...it's previous tenant was... you know,
a woman of the street.

1159
01:23:23,445 --> 01:23:27,745
One night, when I got home a little late.
My wife was alone in the house.

1160
01:23:28,746 --> 01:23:32,046
One of these lowlifes on account of
that woman still being there...

1161
01:23:33,247 --> 01:23:33,947
...enters my house.

1162
01:23:36,748 --> 01:23:38,648
When my wife was
in the bathroom.

1163
01:23:38,949 --> 01:23:40,349
The jerk goes
into the bathroom.

1164
01:23:40,850 --> 01:23:41,650
Who?

1165
01:23:42,151 --> 01:23:43,651
That filthy
son-in-law of yours.

1166
01:23:47,752 --> 01:23:49,752
Now, how do you know
it was Majid?

1167
01:23:49,953 --> 01:23:53,853
When my wife starts screaming,
the guys makes a run for it, but...

1168
01:23:54,754 --> 01:23:56,854
He was in such a hurry that,
he leaves his pickup behind.

1169
01:23:57,355 --> 01:23:59,855
I found him from his pickup.
I went down to where he works.

1170
01:24:01,156 --> 01:24:04,156
I wanted to go there,
grab hold of him...

1171
01:24:06,457 --> 01:24:08,157
...and dishonor him in front
of all his co-workers, but...

1172
01:24:11,658 --> 01:24:12,758
I couldn't bring myself to do it.

1173
01:24:12,859 --> 01:24:15,759
This pickup changes hands
a lot in that store.

1174
01:24:15,760 --> 01:24:17,860
That's why I asked him to come here.
To talk to him, and ask him...

1175
01:24:17,861 --> 01:24:20,661
... if it was him or someone else.

1176
01:24:20,662 --> 01:24:21,862
Majid's not like that...

1177
01:24:23,863 --> 01:24:26,963
if I find out it's been him,
I'll call off everything.

1178
01:24:27,064 --> 01:24:27,964
The wedding and all.

1179
01:24:32,905 --> 01:24:34,665
How's your wife, now?

1180
01:24:37,066 --> 01:24:38,566
I don't know what to say.

1181
01:24:42,167 --> 01:24:43,867
Let me talk to him tonight.

1182
01:24:43,968 --> 01:24:46,168
Give him a call and tell him
I wanna talk to him.

1183
01:24:46,269 --> 01:24:48,669
Tell him to come here,
I wanna ask him who's done it.

1184
01:24:48,670 --> 01:24:51,323
Well, it's just,
they've gone with my wife and daughter

1185
01:24:51,353 --> 01:24:53,170
for "the exchange of vows" shopping.

1186
01:24:54,671 --> 01:24:55,971
Well, at least give him a call.

1187
01:24:56,972 --> 01:24:59,072
Ask him who had his pickup
that night.

1188
01:25:00,672 --> 01:25:01,972
When did this happen?

1189
01:25:02,073 --> 01:25:04,673
About two weeks ago.

1190
01:25:06,974 --> 01:25:11,574
Okay, so you just let me
talk to him tonight... Oh my...

1191
01:25:13,775 --> 01:25:15,775
But, I wanna talk to him,
old man.

1192
01:25:15,976 --> 01:25:20,576
Wait a second, I wanna talk to him.
Call him.

1193
01:25:20,777 --> 01:25:22,977
I don't have his number
in my phone.

1194
01:25:23,378 --> 01:25:24,478
I have it.

1195
01:25:26,579 --> 01:25:29,679
When I say call him to come here,
it's because I don't want to...

1196
01:25:29,680 --> 01:25:31,780
...go down to the store,
make a scene in front of his co-workers.

1197
01:25:31,781 --> 01:25:33,881
You just let me
make sure it's him.

1198
01:25:34,782 --> 01:25:37,782
I have to talk to him in such a way
that I'll get an answer...

1199
01:25:37,783 --> 01:25:39,083
How about I call him myself, huh?

1200
01:25:39,884 --> 01:25:41,684
You want me to do it?

1201
01:25:43,785 --> 01:25:45,185
Okay, let me just
dial his number.

1202
01:25:58,686 --> 01:26:01,886
Hello, Majid? Hi, son...
where are you guys?

1203
01:26:03,187 --> 01:26:05,887
Yeah, I'm here with him.

1204
01:26:08,688 --> 01:26:09,688
Who's with you?

1205
01:26:11,989 --> 01:26:15,889
Listen, when you're alone, gimme a call.
I wanna tell you something.

1206
01:26:18,390 --> 01:26:19,690
Call my cell.

1207
01:26:21,091 --> 01:26:23,791
I don't have it memorized.
Ask Moj'gan.

1208
01:26:25,992 --> 01:26:30,092
Okay... it's nothing...
Bye.

1209
01:26:34,593 --> 01:26:34,793
He said, he'll call when he's alone.

1210
01:26:35,994 --> 01:26:37,894
Say, what do you do yourself?

1211
01:26:39,395 --> 01:26:41,995
I work with this car of Majid's.
His pickup.

1212
01:26:42,496 --> 01:26:45,196
I sell clothes from the
back of the pickup, at nights.

1213
01:26:45,297 --> 01:26:48,197
and I don't come out during the day,
on account of my heart.

1214
01:26:51,198 --> 01:26:54,298
And, how come you don't have
your son-in-law's number?

1215
01:26:54,799 --> 01:26:57,499
Well, I just don't.
Not just him, a lot of people.

1216
01:26:58,400 --> 01:27:00,100
Have you just bought
this number of yours?

1217
01:27:00,401 --> 01:27:01,201
No.

1218
01:27:18,802 --> 01:27:21,702
How come... your son-in-law
doesn't have your number?

1219
01:27:23,003 --> 01:27:25,403
You just told him to
get it from someone else, huh?

1220
01:27:25,904 --> 01:27:27,804
I don't know, man, I don't know.

1221
01:27:28,705 --> 01:27:31,405
I'm so messed up right now that,
I don't even remember my own name.

1222
01:27:34,806 --> 01:27:36,006
Wait a second, old man.

1223
01:27:36,107 --> 01:27:37,907
- It won't open.
- Not so fast. Wait a minute.

1224
01:27:39,909 --> 01:27:41,909
If it's okay, I want you
to take off your shoes.

1225
01:27:42,710 --> 01:27:43,710
What for?

1226
01:27:43,911 --> 01:27:45,511
I wanna see your foot.

1227
01:27:46,712 --> 01:27:48,912
Mister, I'm as old as your father,
you telling me to take off my shoes?

1228
01:27:49,013 --> 01:27:50,613
Open the door, let me go!

1229
01:27:50,914 --> 01:27:52,804
I didn't do anything to you.
Why are you talking like that?

1230
01:27:52,915 --> 01:27:54,615
Take it easy.

1231
01:27:54,816 --> 01:27:57,716
Just take off your shoes for a sec.
Then, I'll open the door for you to leave.

1232
01:27:57,917 --> 01:28:01,217
Why should I take off my shoes?
Open the door!

1233
01:28:01,218 --> 01:28:04,218
Hush! Come here.
Let's go over there.

1234
01:28:14,119 --> 01:28:16,219
Sit on the stair, for a sec,
take off your shoes.

1235
01:28:17,720 --> 01:28:18,220
Sit!

1236
01:28:20,721 --> 01:28:21,321
Sit down!

1237
01:28:24,122 --> 01:28:25,622
Just sit, okay?

1238
01:28:31,323 --> 01:28:32,823
Take off your shoes, please.

1239
01:28:33,124 --> 01:28:34,124
I'm not feeling well, just don't!

1240
01:28:34,425 --> 01:28:35,725
Well, let me help you.

1241
01:28:35,926 --> 01:28:36,926
I'll take it off, okay.

1242
01:28:38,827 --> 01:28:40,527
<i>whispering: I'll take it off.</i>

1243
01:28:47,928 --> 01:28:49,728
The other one,
take off the other one too.

1244
01:28:57,729 --> 01:28:58,729
Your socks too.

1245
01:29:00,630 --> 01:29:02,330
Mister, what do you want from me?

1246
01:29:02,431 --> 01:29:04,331
Take 'em off!
I said, take off your socks.

1247
01:29:04,431 --> 01:29:05,531
Let me do it myself.

1248
01:29:05,732 --> 01:29:07,932
- No!
- Let me!.. just let me!

1249
01:30:22,833 --> 01:30:23,833
Hello, Siavash!

1250
01:30:26,834 --> 01:30:28,734
